### Base
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v4/products

### 1) Get all products - default pagination/sorting
GET {{baseUrl}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2) Get all products - page 0, size 5, sort by name ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=0&size=5&sortBy=name&direction=asc
Accept: application/json

###

### 3) Get all products - page 1, size 5, sort by category descending
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=1&size=5&sortBy=category&direction=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### 4) Get all products - sort by id descending
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=0&size=10&sortBy=id&direction=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### 5) Get all products - sort by createdAt descending
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=0&size=10&sortBy=createdAt&direction=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### 6) Create a product
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 25.50,
  "name": "Gaming Mouse",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 10
}

###

### 7) Create another product
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 12.99,
  "name": "Notebook A5",
  "category": "Office",
  "quantity": 30
}

###

### 8) Create another product
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 89.99,
  "name": "Wireless Headphones",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 8
}

###

### 9) Get product by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/id/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 10) Get product by name - default pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/name/mouse
Accept: application/json

###

### 11) Get product by name - paginated and sorted by name ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}/name/mouse?page=0&size=5&sortBy=name&direction=asc
Accept: application/json

###

### 12) Get product by name - sorted by id descending
GET {{baseUrl}}/name/mouse?page=0&size=10&sortBy=id&direction=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### 13) Get product by category - default pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/electronics
Accept: application/json

###

### 14) Get product by category - page 0, size 5, sort by category ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/electronics?page=0&size=16&sortBy=category&direction=asc
Accept: application/json

###

### 15) Get product by category - page 1, size 3, sort by name descending
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/electronics?page=1&size=3&sortBy=name&direction=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### 16) Get product by price - default pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/price/12
Accept: application/json

###

### 17) Get product by price - page 0, size 5, sort by id ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}/price/25?page=0&size=5&sortBy=id&direction=asc
Accept: application/json

###

### 18) Get product by price - sort by name descending
GET {{baseUrl}}/price/30?page=0&size=10&sortBy=name&direction=desc
Accept: application/json

###

### 19) Update product by ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/1
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 49.99,
  "name": "Gaming Mouse Pro",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 15
}

###

### 20) Patch product as seen
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/seen/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 21) Patch product as paid
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/paid/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 22) Delete product by ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/1
Accept: application/json

###

### 23) Try to get missing product by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/id/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### 24) Validation test - empty name
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 15.00,
  "name": "",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 5
}

###

### 25) Validation test - empty category
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 15.00,
  "name": "Keyboard",
  "category": "",
  "quantity": 5
}

###

### 26) Validation test - quantity = 0
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 15.00,
  "name": "Keyboard",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 0
}

###

### 27) Validation test - negative price
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": -5.00,
  "name": "Bad Product",
  "category": "Electronics",
  "quantity": 3
}

###

### 28) Validation test - invalid enum category
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 15.00,
  "name": "Keyboard",
  "category": "InvalidCategory",
  "quantity": 5
}

###

### 29) Get by invalid enum category
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/invalidCategory
Accept: application/json

###

### 30) Update non-existing product
PUT {{baseUrl}}/9999
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "price": 20.00,
  "name": "Updated Missing Product",
  "category": "Office",
  "quantity": 2
}

###

### 31) Delete non-existing product
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### 32) Patch seen for non-existing product
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/seen/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### 33) Patch paid for non-existing product
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/paid/9999
Accept: application/json

###

### 34) Invalid sort field test
### Your service currently falls back to id
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=0&size=10&sortBy=wrongField&direction=asc
Accept: application/json

###

### 35) Invalid direction test
### Your service currently falls back silently to ascending
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=0&size=10&sortBy=name&direction=wrong
Accept: application/json

###

### 36) Large page size test
### Your service currently caps size at 50
GET {{baseUrl}}?page=0&size=100&sortBy=id&direction=asc
Accept: application/json

###

### 37) Category search using lowercase enum input
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/office
Accept: application/json

###

### 38) Category search using uppercase enum input
GET {{baseUrl}}/category/OFFICE
Accept: application/json